# CLAUDE.md Template — Project Knowledge

Use this template to structure your project's `CLAUDE.md` for persistent knowledge
that should be available in every Claude Code session. Copy the sections you need
into your project's `CLAUDE.md` and fill them in.

The `/session save --learn` option can automatically suggest additions to these sections.

---

## Project Overview

- **What**: [One sentence — what does this project do?]
- **Stack**: [Languages, frameworks, databases, key dependencies]
- **Repo structure**: [Brief layout, e.g. "src/ = backend, frontend/ = React app, infra/ = Terraform"]

## Architecture

- [Key architectural decisions and why they were made]
- [How components connect — e.g. "API → PostgreSQL, frontend → API via REST"]
- [Patterns used — e.g. "repository pattern for DB access", "event-driven via Redis pub/sub"]

## Conventions

- [Naming conventions, code style, commit message format]
- [Branch strategy, PR process]
- [File organization patterns]

## Environment & Setup

- [How to run locally — required env vars, Docker, etc.]
- [Test commands and prerequisites]
- [Non-obvious setup quirks — e.g. "needs Docker running for integration tests"]

## Discoveries & Gotchas

- [Undocumented behavior — e.g. "auth middleware swallows errors silently"]
- [Surprising dependencies or coupling]
- [Things that look wrong but are intentional]
- [Performance pitfalls or known limitations]

## Key Decisions Log

| Date | Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| YYYY-MM-DD | [What was decided] | [Why] |

---

### Tips

- Keep entries concise — bullet points over prose
- Date your entries so you know when decisions were made
- Remove entries that are no longer true
- This file is loaded into every session, so don't let it grow unbounded — aim for < 200 lines
